<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Minutes of meeting – 10 December 2009</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from the Professional Standards Authority for Health</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">and</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Social Care (NMC </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">0011</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">)</span></p><h1 style="margin:20pt 0pt 12pt 35.45pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><a name="title"></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction</span></h1><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Professional Standards Authority for Health and Social Care is pleased to provide the Health Committee with written evidence on the Nursing and Midwifery Council. Our evidence focuses on the work of the NMC since its last accountability hearing (9 October 2012). </span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">This is the first submission from the Authority under the arrangements described by the Committee in its recent report </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">After Francis: making a difference</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, whereby the Committee will take evidence from the Authority on the performance of each regulator and draw on this in preparing for regular accountability hearings. </span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In June 2013 we laid our 2012/13 Performance Review before Parliament. This provided the Authority’s assessment of the NMC’s performance against 24 Standards of Good Regulation in the 2012/13 financial year. We were grateful for the opportunity to discuss our findings with the Committee on 9 July 2013. </span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">This Memorandum supplements and complements the findings of our 2012/13 Performance Review. This paper also discusses other recently announced developments in the NMC’s regulatory work and its response to our 2012 Strategic Review. We highlight areas that the Committee may wish to examine further in their meeting with the NMC:</span></h2><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 45.97pt; padding-left:10.73pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Performance against the Standards of Good Regulation</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 45.97pt; padding-left:10.73pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Section 29 scrutiny of fitness to practise decisions</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 45.97pt; padding-left:10.73pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Assuring the continuing fitness to practise of registrants (revalidation)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 45.97pt; padding-left:10.73pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Reviewing and refreshing policies and procedures</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 45.97pt; padding-left:10.73pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Governance, openness and transparency.</span></li></ul><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">1.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Our scrutiny and oversight of the NMC continues. We have recently audited the NMC’s handling of 100 cases closed at the initial stages of its fitness to practise process without a final hearing, and we particularly sampled cases relating to nurses working at Mid Staffordshire NHS Foundation Trust. Our report on this audit is in preparation and we will send a copy to the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Committee when it is published.</span></h2><h1 style="margin:20pt 0pt 12pt 35.45pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">NMC’s response to Strategic Review</span></h1><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The performance of the NMC across its regulatory functions, governance and operations has fallen short of the Standards of Good Regulation, and wider public expectation since before 2008. In July 2012 we published a Strategic Review of the organisation, at the request of the Under Secretary of State for Health. This concluded that many of the organisation’s past failures arose because the organisation did not properly understand its regulatory purpose and because of its lack of clear, consistent strategic direction. </span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We made 14 recommendations for improvement at the NMC in the Strategic Review Final Report. In our view the NMC have taken these seriously. They have consistently told us and others that they do and it is clear that they have acted on them. We have not been asked to formally review their progress by Ministers and therefore have not carried out any detailed analysis of the organisation’s progress against each recommendation. Accordingly we offer only our general impression of progress over the first 14 months of their two year turnaround programme. </span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The NMC began acting on our recommendations immediately. A reconstituted Council was appointed and met for the first time in May 2013. Since this time we see improvement in the quality of papers and discussions of the Council and consider that the new Council demonstrates a more business-like grip. </span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In the context of the recommendations made in our Strategic Review, it is our view that there are still some important milestones to be achieved over the remaining 10 months. For example the new Council is to review its strategic direction, is developing its performance management information to support its six new key performance indicators, and is to implement the recently agreed quality assurance strategy. The NMC is managing some important risks, and there is some evidence of improvement in fitness to practise processes, but there is still work to be done in improving registration. The Committee may wish to establish what the NMC anticipates will be achieved by June 2014. </span></h2><h1 style="margin:20pt 0pt 12pt 35.45pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Key underlying themes: risk and purpose</span></h1><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">For the Authority, two themes consistently emerge in our assessment of the NMC’s performance and their on-going response to our Strategic Review. First, how is the NMC assessing the risks posed by the professions they regulate and using this evidence in developing current and future work? Accurate risk assessment will rely upon management information systems that support the business of regulation efficiently and effectively. Historically this has been an area of concern with the NMC and we are keen to see improvement. </span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Secondly, how well does the NMC deliver its regulatory obligations? We reported in our 2012/13 Performance Review: ‘The NMC has stated that public protection is now central to its approach and that public protection is the “litmus test” against which all current and proposed work is now measured.’ This renewed focus is encouraging, but in our view, the test against which the NMC’s work must be judged is broader, and should reflect its full regulatory purpose. As well as protecting the public, it is essential that current and future work also upholds professional standards and maintains public confidence, both in the profession and in the regulatory process.</span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We commented in the Performance Review that, ‘we are concerned that the NMC has not yet been able to identify measures to assess whether or not that “[litmus] test” has been passed’. Whether this is the narrow test of public protection, or the broader test that we advocate, it is essential that assessment measures are identified swiftly by the NMC, if confidence in the organisation and its performance is to grow and be sustained. The Committee may be interested to find out more about how the NMC assures itself that its work now and in the future is meeting this test. </span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">3.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">These two themes – assessing and responding to the risks, and meeting the three-fold purpose of regulation – recur throughout the following discussions of the NMC’s recent work.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></h2><h1 style="margin:20pt 0pt 12pt 35.45pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Findings from the 2012/13 Performance Review</span></h1><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">4.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">As we reported to the Committee in July, in our most recent Performance Review we found that the NMC had not met seven of our 24 Standards of Good Regulation. One further standard was only met inconsistently. The seven unmet standards are listed below:</span></h2><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 49.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Through the regulator’s continuing professional development/revalidation systems, registrants maintain the standards required to stay fit to practise</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 49.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The registration process, including the management of appeals, is fair, based on the regulator’s standards, efficient, transparent, secure, and continuously improving</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 49.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">All fitness to practise complaints are reviewed on receipt and serious cases are prioritised and where appropriate referred to an interim orders panel</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 49.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Fitness to practise cases are dealt with as quickly as possible taking into account the complexity and type of case and the conduct of both sides. Delays do not result in harm or potential harm to patients. Where necessary the regulator protects the public by means of interim orders</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 49.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">All parties to a fitness to practise case are kept updated on the progress of their case and supported to participate effectively in the process</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 49.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">All fitness to practise decisions made at the initial and final stages of the process are well reasoned, consistent, protect the public and maintain confidence in the profession</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 49.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Information about fitness to practise cases is securely retained.</span></li></ol><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">4.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The NMC has not met (3), (6) and (7) in all Performance Reviews since 2010/11. Their continued failure to meet standards around prioritising complaints and making well-reasoned decisions illustrates, in our view, the difficulties they have in assessing and responding to the risks presented by their registrants. The inability to meet the standard around information security reflects their shortfalls in assessing and managing the risks presented by their own processes.</span></h2><h1 style="margin:20pt 0pt 12pt 35.45pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Our s29 case scrutiny </span></h1><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">5.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Committee discussed the Authority’s scrutiny of final fitness to practise decisions with the NMC in October 2012 (s29 scrutiny). Paragraphs 36-39 of the Committee’s March 2013 report on the NMC discussed s29 referrals. It included reference to NMC evidence that there have been ‘no s29 referrals of its decisions by the CHRE (or its successor the PSA) since September 2010’. </span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 3pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="display:inline; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline">5.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We would like to highlight to the Committee that this statement does not match our records. The table below provides details of the total number of case meetings</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> across all regulators, the number of NMC case meetings and the number of NMC appeals in 2010–2012, and to date in 2013.</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></h2><div style="text-align:center"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin:0 auto"><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:94.85pt"><p style="margin:6pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:103.45pt"><p style="margin:6pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Total case meetings held</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:120pt"><p style="margin:6pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Total NMC case meetings held</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-